    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-fda-cdrh-modeling-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is acknowledged; the assessment team accepts this gap given that ASTM F1717 prescribes a single standardized test configuration and the regulatory context does not require multi-condition testing for this device class. All three QoIs satisfy the pre-established E/uval < 1.96 and < 10% difference acceptance criteria. The FEA modeling framework is judged credible for its intended use in supporting the 510(k) submission for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct.",
